BACKGROUNDS- 

background-color
background-image
background-repeat
background-attachment
background-position
background

body{
    background-color: lightblue;
}
to change opacity of background we use opacity 
body{
    background-color:blue;
    opacity:0.3;
}
in RGB
in rgb there is a 4th attribute called opacity rgb(0,10,20, 0.3)

to add image to the background
body{
    background-image: url("paper.gif");
}
h1{
    bacground-image: url("first.gif")
}

background repeat
body{
    background-image: url("school.jpg")
    background-repeat: repeat-x;
}
body{
    background-image: url("school.jpg")
    background-repeat: repeat-y;
}
 background-repeat: no-repeat;

 to change the position of the background position-
 body{
    background-image: url("university.jpeg")
    background-repeat: repeat-y;
    background position:right top;
 }

 Background Attachment-
 makes sure if the background image ahould scroll or be fixed- 
 body{
    background-image: url("university.jpeg")
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: right top;
    background-attachment: fixed;

 }
body{
    background-image: url("white.jpeg");

}

instead of writting entire background attributes we could write
body{
    background: #ffffff url("white.jpeg") no-repeat scroll top right;
}
 order is 
 colour
 url
 repeat
 attachment
 position

 CSS BORDERS- borders
 border-style property 
 values allowed- 
 dotted
 dashed
 solid
 double
 groove
 ridge
 inset
 outset
 none hidden

 border-style
 border-width in px
 .one{
    border-style: double;
    border-width: 5px;
 }
  to change width on top borders and bottom borders- 
  p.one{
    border-style: ridge;
    border-width: 20px 5 px;
  }
20 px would be top and bottom border part and 5px would be sides border part

BORDER COLOR-
.one{
    border-style: double;
    border-color: red;
}
to have different border color for different sides- 
.one{
    border-style: ridge;
    border-color: red green blue yellow;
}

CSS BORDER SHORTHAND PROPERTY- 
means without giving border-width border-style border-color again and again we can just say 
border: 5px ridge blue;

border-width
border-style
border-color

ROUNDED BORDERS- 
round borders are of 3 types- 
round 
rounder 

we do by using a border-radius

.one{
    border: 5px solid red;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

