 CASCADING 
 order is important in css 

specificity in CSS- 
start at 0 
add 100 for each ID Value
add 10 for each Class Value 
add 1 for each element selector
add 1000 for inline css

for example- 
p -- 1
p.test -- 10+1 = 11
p#demo -- 100+1 = 101
<p style="color:pink;">- 1000

INHERITANCE -
<div>
<p>hello world!</p>
</div>

here div is the parent and p is the child. so if we change properties of div properties of p will also change. 

inherit- gives the same color as the parent.
like color: inherit;
 
!important- important is a keyword we put after the value to increase its specificity by 1000 like
h1{
    color: red;
}
h1{
    color: blue !important;
}
 here color will be blue 


OVERFLOW- 
overflow:visible;
