overflow: scroll;
overflow: auto; (same as scroll)

object-fit: contain;

cursor - to change what kind of pointer would go on the button or any element

to center any body just do 
margin:auto;
width:50%;

ADVANCED CSS PROPERTIES- 
 
clip path generator- to change the shape of images

box-sizing:

responsiveness- 
making sure of the layout in every device 

media queries- 

@media media-type

@media screen and (max-width:600px) and (orientation: landscape)

for body- 
margin
padding
border
background

margin- things outside border 
padding- area around the content 
width and height are used to increase the content area not the area around the content 

css outline- 
outline is outside the border 
outline style- solid/double/ridge
outline-width- thin is typically 1px
medium is typically 3px
and thick is typically 5px

shorthand property of outline- 

outline: width style color;

outline offset adds space between border and outline

flexbox - 

to position a flex container 
main axis- horizontal axis 
cross-axis- vertical axis 

Display BLOCK ==
display:block; = vertical 
display: flex; = horizotal 

justify content : space center;
justify-content:space around;

align-items: stretch;

flex-wrap: wrap;
boxes will wrap as the screen size decreases
